17/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Two international teams launched inspections of the Macedonian Army, the defence ministry announced Tuesday (16 March). 
The visits are part of the commitments of the signatory countries, including Macedonia, under Vienna Document 99.
In other news Tuesday, Czech Prime Minister Vladimir Spidla arrived on a four-day visit to Macedonia. 
The focus will be on enhancing bilateral economic ties. 
(MIA, Makfax - 17/03/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 16/03/04)
